<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871109-0002 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Southmark Corp.</HL><DD> 11/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SRVI SMTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   Southmark Corp., Dallas, is offering to purchase as much as 32.9% of the common shares outstanding of Servico Inc. for $11 a share, or $13.8 million.    Today in The Wall Street Journal, Southmark, a real estate and financial services concern, said the offer for as many as 1,250,000 shares will expire at 12:01 a.m. EST Dec. 8.    Servico, West Palm Beach, Fla., owns and operates hotels and inns.    Servico stock closed at $10.50, up 25 cents, in national over-the-counter trading Friday. Southmark stock closed at $5.625, down 12.5 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. </TEXT></DOC>